  6. Conveying Non-Source Forms.

  You may convey a covered work in object code form under the terms
of sections 4 and 5, provided that you also convey the
machine-readable Corresponding Source under the terms of this License,
in one of these ways:

  a) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
  (including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by the
  Corresponding Source fixed on a durable physical medium
  customarily used for software interchange.

  b) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
  (including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by a
  written offer, valid for at least three years and valid for as
  long as you offer spare parts and customer support for that product
  model, to give anyone who possesses the object code either (1) a
  copy of the Corresponding Source for all the software in the
  product that is covered by this License, on a customizable
  medium customarily used for software interchange, for a price
  no more than your reasonable cost of physically performing this
  conveying of source, or (2) access to copy the
  Corresponding Source from a network server at no charge.

  c) Convey individual copies of the object code with a copy of the
  written offer to provide the Corresponding Source.  This
  alternative is allowed only occasionally and noncommercially, and
  only if you received the object code with the corresponding offer
  to satisfy section 6.

  d) Convey the object code by offering access from a designated
  place (gratis or for a fee), and offer equivalent access to the
  Corresponding Source in the same way through the same place at no
  further charge.  You need not require recipients to copy the
  Corresponding Source along with the object code.  If the place to
  copy the object code is a network server, the correspondence between
  the object code and Corresponding Source may be direct, or
  managed by a third party.  (This alternative is allowed only if
  you receive the object code with the corresponding offer.)

  e) Convey the object code using peer-to-peer transmission, provided
  you inform other peers where the object code and Corresponding
  Source of the object code are being offered to the general public
  at no charge under section 6.

  A separable portion of the object code, whose source code is excluded
from the Corresponding Source as a System Library, need not be
included in conveying the object code work.

  A user-interface may provide additional appropriate legal notices,
beyond those required by section 3, if it is not a mere plug-in.
However, if the work is a standalone work that includes such a interface,
the interface must display Appropriate Legal Notices.  However, if the
Program has interactive interfaces that do not display Appropriate
